OL,7,FMichael Phillips, from Age Cymru says
OL,8,F"there is a concern that with Winter
OL,9,Fapproaching, people may decide to keep
OL,10,Ftheir heating off, or cut back on
OL,11,Ffood, and make themselves seriously
OL,12,Fill, which would present even more
OL,13,Fproblems for our beleaguered health
OL,14,Fand social services.
OL,16,F"We have to remember that many older
OL,17,Fpeople require more heating because
OL,18,Fthey are housebound, or have serious
OL,19,Fillnesses that require a warm home."
